messages.ssml: <speak>The Center for Disease Control and Prevention recommends that you cover your mouth and nose with a cloth when you go out. Children under age 2 and people who have trouble breathing or might not be able to take off their own mask shouldn't wear one. Don't wear a mask intended for health care workers and always continue to keep at least 6 feet away from other people, even when wearing a mask.</speak>
